<bibRefCitation id="E8A54D326985C440DFFB8F82171568B3" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="30" pageNumber="113" pagination="405 - 414" refId="B25" refString="Hara, H, 2012. Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 18: 405 - 414" title="Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia." volume="18" year="2012">Hara (2012)</bibRefCitation>
: holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="3605C051765D7B9223963BD0E8CF61EE" authority="Fallén, 1829" authorityName="Fallén" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Phyllotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phyllotoma fasciata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">Phyllotoma fasciata</taxonomicName>
examined, redescription, hosts, biology, first records from Japan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AFBC672DCCBA5C841CEDE84971845830" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="832EF80623AEA3A22EACC95BFD4C1D5C" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="870A43CE6854D164AE03A427EE359330" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
Japan: Hokkaido: 1♀ (DEI-GISHym19669), Bibai, Koshunai, 
<geoCoordinate id="F4784A87369914BB26C130ECDE1FA5E5" degrees="43.29950" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="43.2995">43.29950N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="F3EBB63471D82A501BEFD553E155E2B1" degrees="141.84940" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="141.8494">141.84940E</geoCoordinate>
, reared 
<taxonomicName id="0405878C09D5DE85F0626C6BC31D4DD1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Populus suaveolens" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suaveolens">
<emphasis id="2441FC03997ED7144A9FEEA156D34DB1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Populus suaveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 16.08.2010 (emergence date), leg. H. Hara (SDEI).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72B4DE284AABE32523FB0F94C1657126" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Russia: Tuva Republic: 1♀ (DEI-GISHym83889), East Sayan Mountains, Black Irkut, river shingle and rocks, 1691m, 30.06.2012, leg. W.-H. Liebig (SDEI).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F418F9DD5EF02E64CFCBF7082B7024A" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" type="host">
<paragraph id="86DDDBDC4250C9856409F9A21C268F2B" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Host plants and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4F5F749ABD9821A35484D5DE7DF0964" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
Published host plant records are 
<taxonomicName id="EF7EDFFB28CBA5028C5966B509477E12" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Populus suaveolens" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suaveolens">
<emphasis id="B2F53D2224FD999190D5190AC81BC8A1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Populus suaveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fisch. ex Poiteau &amp; A. Vilm. (
<bibRefCitation id="FB4DBCCF6A2E9AEF9F98432BA912E57E" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="30" pageNumber="113" pagination="405 - 414" refId="B25" refString="Hara, H, 2012. Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 18: 405 - 414" title="Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia." volume="18" year="2012">Hara 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2D92F4F9534624FD1EE1240790AB9A38" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1134/S1995425518060033" author="Kirichenko, NI" journalOrPublisher="Contemporary Problems of Ecology" pageId="31" pageNumber="114" pagination="576 - 593" refId="B33" refString="Kirichenko, NI, Skvortsova, MV, Petko, VM, Ponomarenko, MG, Lopez-Vaamonde, C, 2018. Salicaceae-Feeding Leaf-Mining Insects in Siberia: Distribution, Trophic Specialization, and Pest Status. Contemporary Problems of Ecology 11: 576 - 593" title="Salicaceae-Feeding Leaf-Mining Insects in Siberia: Distribution, Trophic Specialization, and Pest Status." url="https://doi.org/10.1134/S1995425518060033" volume="11" year="2018">Kirichenko et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="59DF201EC2057C660B536926BD01C3B3" genus="P." lsidName="P. nigra" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="E54808EEEE31CE5792EA1A673D44791F" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">P. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<bibRefCitation id="A9C0379603D117DF7741961EA68D74A6" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="30" pageNumber="113" pagination="405 - 414" refId="B25" refString="Hara, H, 2012. Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 18: 405 - 414" title="Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia." volume="18" year="2012">Hara 2012</bibRefCitation>
). According to the images associated with the reared specimen from the Moscow Region (see below), 
<taxonomicName id="02B67DE4F2A1F2DAC267148EB9AE8384" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Populus balsamifera" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balsamifera">
<emphasis id="DA56581421FE2C1DBEA1222E3F2FE37D" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Populus balsamifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. is also a host. No males have yet been found. The cocoon remains within the leaf. Possibly multivoltine (
<bibRefCitation id="FF6DDAFC72B990FC8D9EEDFD9758963C" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="30" pageNumber="113" pagination="405 - 414" refId="B25" refString="Hara, H, 2012. Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 18: 405 - 414" title="Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia." volume="18" year="2012">Hara 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C7C51BFF9C326DD3112B71CD103A04AD" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1C380ED2990794C660B3050660558C27" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B64646BAFF032D063389A8017687211" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
The previously known distribution comprises Japan (Hokkaido: 
<bibRefCitation id="0565E4645CAE2E023CEFA62935C49FF9" author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="30" pageNumber="113" pagination="405 - 414" refId="B25" refString="Hara, H, 2012. Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 18: 405 - 414" title="Heterarthrusfasciatus (Hymenoptera, Tenthredinidae), a Leaf-mining Sawfly of Populus spp. in Northeast Asia." volume="18" year="2012">Hara 2012</bibRefCitation>
), Kamtchatka (
<bibRefCitation id="61FDC1B576754FB7B59D5D716745AC9D" author="Malaise, R" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen zur Larvalsystematik der Insekten" pageId="32" pageNumber="115" refId="B51" refString="Malaise, R, 1931. Entomologische Ergebnisse der schwedischen Kamtchatka Expedition 1920-1922. (35. Tenthredinidae). [Separatum]. Arkiv foer Zoologi 23 (2[A8]): 1-68." title="Entomologische Ergebnisse der schwedischen Kamtchatka Expedition 1920 - 1922. (35. Tenthredinidae). [Separatum]. Arkiv foer Zoologi 23 (2 [A 8]): 1 - 68." year="1931">Malaise 1931</bibRefCitation>
), and East Siberia (Buryat Republic: 
<bibRefCitation id="861E2D4F63BEE8D4129221A27AAFE216" author="Sundukov, YN" editor="Belokobylskij, SA" journalOrPublisher="Trudy Zoologiceskogo Instituta Rossijskoj Akademii Nauk, Supplement" pageId="33" pageNumber="116" pagination="20 - 117" refId="B68" refString="Sundukov, YN, 2017. Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and Wood Wasps. In: Belokobylskij, SA, Lelej, AS, Eds., Annotated Catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia (Volume 1). Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. . Trudy Zoologiceskogo Instituta Rossijskoj Akademii Nauk, Supplement 6: 20 - 117" title="Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and Wood Wasps." volume="6" volumeTitle="Annotated Catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia (Volume 1). Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata." year="2017">Sundukov 2017</bibRefCitation>
; Novosibirsk and Irkutsk Oblasts: 
<bibRefCitation id="283D252F84DA675CDE4838B23A7B9B92" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1134/S1995425518060033" author="Kirichenko, NI" journalOrPublisher="Contemporary Problems of Ecology" pageId="31" pageNumber="114" pagination="576 - 593" refId="B33" refString="Kirichenko, NI, Skvortsova, MV, Petko, VM, Ponomarenko, MG, Lopez-Vaamonde, C, 2018. Salicaceae-Feeding Leaf-Mining Insects in Siberia: Distribution, Trophic Specialization, and Pest Status. Contemporary Problems of Ecology 11: 576 - 593" title="Salicaceae-Feeding Leaf-Mining Insects in Siberia: Distribution, Trophic Specialization, and Pest Status." url="https://doi.org/10.1134/S1995425518060033" volume="11" year="2018">Kirichenko et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="044EB068919995C897065A9C30F50E26" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heterarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heterarthrus fasciatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis id="91E30C950FD52CE4AAC02B82B133715E" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Heterarthrus fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs in European Russia, based on images by Andrej Ponomarev of a reared female. The specimen, misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="2351265DE66A3E6E7E425BFA90076B90" genus="H." lsidName="H. ochropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="ochropoda">
<emphasis id="65B4778D1382B9E1932843307A542EAD" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">H. ochropoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is illustrated on the website 
<taxonomicName id="BB9EAD050B3DB093D19AACDCD44017AC" class="insecta" lsidName="" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" rank="class">insecta</taxonomicName>
.pro (
<taxonomicName id="8D7CDCB839B7EBC1E519AEB13289F349" class="insecta" lsidName="" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" rank="class">insecta</taxonomicName>
.pro/), accessed on 27.03.2019: photos [adult] #68936-68938, [leaf-mines] #68930-68935. The photos are labelled [transliterated]: Moskovskaja obl., Orehovo-Zuevskij r-n, pos. Topolinyj, na topole, with date for one image of leaf-mine 04.07.2014.
</paragraph>
